column5: Anyone having any luck on the Notty? I've been out twice ( in Wasaga) but no hits. Frank
Yup. He is right on the money. The poor man hasn't caught a fish there in years.  Just goes to look at the pretty trees at this time of year. Comes back and goes again. When will he ever learn!
Lol lots of fish up stream in the notty Pm me I'll give u some tips
Youre fishing the wrong area. With warm water, early season steelhead fly through rivers until it gets cold; move upstream.
he goes where "no other man has ever gone before" May cost you an extra $40.00 if you are not careful. BillM lives with the gods
he goes where "no other man has ever gone before" May cost you an extra $40.00 if you are not careful. BillM lives with the gods  All the fish are in my bathtub.
Ya wasaga is the wrong area  stay away lol.
Ya wasaga is the wrong area stay away lol.  It's definitely not typical steelhead water and if you don't catch a pod of fish you'll be having a fun day doing nothing, lol.
It's defiantly not holding water that's for sure.  Not the easiest fish for a novice steelheader.
Just fire me a pm and I'll let you know where Billm was parked Tuesday and Wednesday afternnoon.....                             Nah just kidding...
Thanks for the morning chuckle fellas.   Where ever Bill is parked,I just go bye. The next spot will be much better.LOL
